HEADWORD: Hydride
<hw>Hy"dride</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hydr-</ets> +
<ets>ide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A compound of the binary
type, in which hydrogen is united with some other element.</def><--
spec., with a more electropositive element --></p>

<p><cs><col><b>lith"i*um hy"dride</b></col> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <cd>A hydride of lithium, <chform>LiH</chform>,
commonly used as a powerful reducing agent in organic
chemistry.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydriform</ent>⟦br⟧
